---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import VideoHero from "../components/VideoHero.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Victims Affected by Thomas Anders - Cancelled Concerts 2023"
  lang="es"
>
  <section
    id="warning"
    class="bg-red-50 p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg border border-red-200 mb-8 sm:mb-12"
  >
    <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold mb-3 sm:mb-4 text-red-700">
      ⚠️ Warning
    </h2>
    <p class="text-red-700 text-base sm:text-lg">
      We warn all fans planning to purchase tickets through Tix4Us (a new company by Vahe Shahinian) that there is a high risk of falling victim to a scam similar to the one that occurred in Spain.

      You can find more information on this website dedicated to Thomas Anders fans who were scammed by the company It’s My Seat, linked to Vahe Shahinian.
    </p>
  </section>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <VideoHero videoUrl="/videos/intro-en.mp4" />

    <section class="mb-8 sm:mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-4 sm:mb-6">
        Platform for Affected Concert-Goers
      </h2>
      <div class="prose max-w-none">
        <p class="mb-4 text-base sm:text-lg">
          In 2023, thousands of fans were affected by the cancellation of three Thomas Anders and Sandra concerts in Spain: Barcelona, Bilbao, and Seville. Not only were we unable to see the artists, but we also lost the money invested in the tickets.

        </p>
        <p class="mb-4 text-base sm:text-lg">
          It's my seat, the company responsible for ticket sales, refuses to refund the affected fans. The person in charge, Vahe Shahinian, has created a new company called Tix4Us which, surprisingly, is organizing Thomas Anders concerts in the United States and Canada while still owing thousands of euros to Spanish fans.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8 sm:mb-12" id="noticias">
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold mb-4 sm:mb-6">
        News and Updates
      </h2>

      <div class="bg-white p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
          Fine in ¨País Vasco¨
        </h3>
        <p class="text-base">
          The Basque authorities have fined the company, but this does not guarantee the refund of money to those affected.
        </p>
        <a
          href="https://www.radionervion.com/2024/02/06/denuncian-a-la-promotora-de-los-conciertos-de-sandra-y-modern-talking/"
          class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
          target="_blank"
        >
          Leer más
        </a>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md mb-6">
        <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold mb-2">
          More legal issues of Vahe Shahinian        </h3>
        <p class="text-base">
          Legal cases where It´s My Seat are involved
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5">
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://casetext.com/case/its-my-seat-inc-v-ein-cap-inc"
              class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
              target="_blank"
            >
            Case Ein Cap Inc.
            </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a
              href="https://casetext.com/case/its-my-seat-inc-v-woodley"
              class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
              target="_blank"
            >
            Case Woodley
          </a>
          </li>
          <li>
            <a
              href="http://www.metnews.com/articles/2023/noorderviolated_100523.htm"
              class="text-blue-600 hover:underline"
              target="_blank"
            >
            LA contracts issues
          </a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8 sm:mb-12" id="multimedia">
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold mb-4 sm:mb-6">Multimedia</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-10 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="bg-white p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Videos</h3>
          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">
                Concert Scam. Warning
              </h4>
              <div class="aspect-video">
                <video class="w-full h-full rounded" controls>
                  <source
                    src="/src/assets/video 1 inglés estafa concierto.mp4"
                    type="video/mp4"
                  />
                  Your browser does not support the video tag.
                </video>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">
                Understanding the scam in less than 2 minutes
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">
                Disappointing explanation from Thomas Anders
              </h4>
              <div class="aspect-video">
                <!-- Incrustar el video de YouTube -->
                <iframe
                  width="388"
                  height="250"
                  src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/-azjSMBAKQ0?si=NyzlTA51Tlg33G4S"
                  title="YouTube video player"
                  frameborder="0"
                  allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
                  referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
                  allowfullscreen></iframe>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">
                Thomas Anders says that ticket refunds must be requested from the point of purchase. Lies!
              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">
                KissFM promoting the scam, including their DJ Tony Peret.
              </h4>
              <div class="aspect-video">
                <!-- Incrustar el video de YouTube -->
                <iframe
                  width="388"
                  height="250"
                  src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/UOvyXxaxWF8?si=Ul2U0H-hrkv0rBIc"
                  title="YouTube video player"
                  frameborder="0"
                  allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
                  referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
                  allowfullscreen></iframe>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">
                Could they be part of the scam?              </p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h4 class="font-medium mb-2">
                EGB FM also promoting the scam.
              </h4>
              <div class="aspect-video">
                <!-- Incrustar el video de YouTube -->
                <iframe
                  width="388"
                  height="250"
                  src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/BZtL6rwp10A?si=dx4kDpKQre1HwzPE" title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">
                Aren't they ashamed?
              </p>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold mb-4">
            Images Gallery
          </h3>
          <div class="grid gap-4 sm:gap-6">
            <div class="bg-white p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
              <img
                src="public/images/cartel.jpg"
                alt="Evidencia 1"
                class="w-full h-50 object-cover rounded-lg"
              />
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">
                With this sign, they deceived us all.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
              <img
                src="public/images/sevilla.png"
                alt="Evidencia 2"
                class="w-full h-50 object-cover rounded-lg"
              />
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">
                If the NODO in Seville participated in the promotion, don’t they care that it all ended up being a scam?              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
              <img
                src="public/images/badalona.png"
                alt="Evidencia 3"
                class="w-full h-50 object-cover rounded-lg"
              />
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">
                Does the Olimpic Arena in Badalona have nothing to say to the attendees?
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
              <img
                src="public/images/bilbao.png"
                alt="Evidencia 4"
                class="w-full h-50 object-cover rounded-lg"
              />
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">
                And what about the Biskaia Arena?
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-8 sm:mb-12" id="evidencias">
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-bold mb-4 sm:mb-6">Involved Parties </h2>
      <div class="grid gap-4 sm:gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="bg-white p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold mb-3 sm:mb-4">Thomas Anders</h3>
          <p>
            A former music star lends his image so that fans in Spain are deceived with the illusion of attending his concerts, only to be scammed when the concerts are canceled without any refund.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold mb-3 sm:mb-4">Vahe Shahinian</h3>
          <p>
            A figure dedicated to scamming fans in Spain through his company "It’s My Seat" is now trying to deceive fans in Canada and the United States through a new company called "Tix4Us." </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold mb-3 sm:mb-4">It´s My Seat</h3>
          <p>
            A company through whose website, the individual known as Vahe Shahinian carries out his scams. Attempts to contact this company for a ticket refund have been futile.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold mb-3 sm:mb-4">Tix4Us</h3>
          <p>
            Vahe Shahinian is using this new platform to promote Thomas Anders' concerts in Canada and the United States. Extreme caution is necessary, as these people have no problem canceling just days before the event and keeping the money from ticket sales.          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold mb-3 sm:mb-4">KissFM y EGB FM</h3>
          <p>
            Spanish radio stations don’t seem to care about the listeners who fell into Vahe Shahinian’s trap, even after they promoted him on their networks. KissFM actively participated in the concert promotions, featuring DJ Tony Peret, who was set to perform at these events.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white p-4 sm:p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md">
          <h3 class="text-lg sm:text-xl font-semibold mb-3 sm:mb-4">Consumer Associations and Government (Regional and National)</h3>
          <p>
            Spain has numerous consumer associations that receive public funding, yet none have stepped up to protect the scammed Thomas Anders fans. For some reason, they are uninterested in ensuring ticket refunds. Only a single complaint was filed, which resulted in a fine—but that money doesn’t go back to the scammed fans; instead, it goes to the government that issued the fine.
            
            Spain even has a Ministry of Consumer Affairs, yet there has been no response. Spain is a prime target for these types of scammers because fans are left defenseless.          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>

